lzh_formatted:
  title: 長峴下人家
  author: 金宗直
  language: lzh
  text: 籬外紅桃竹數科。𩁺𩁺雨脚閒飛花。老翁荷耒兒騎犢。子美詩中西崦家。
korean:
  title: 장현 하인가
  author: 김종직
  language: kor
  text: |-
    울타리 밖에는 붉은 복사꽃과 대나무 두어 가지
    부실부실 빗발은 가끔 꽃을 날린다
    늙은 첨지는 보습을 졌고 아이는 송아지를 탔나니
    이것은 자미의 시 가운데 서암의 집일러라
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1450_020_0460&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: 'Below Long Peak: A Rustic Home'
  author: Kim Jong-jik
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Beyond the fence, red peach blossoms and bamboo stalks,
    Soft rain-threads drift and scatter petals in their flight.
    The old man carries his plow, the boy rides his calf—
    A scene from Tu Fu's verse, the western valley's humble house.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: Tu Fu (杜甫), the celebrated Tang Dynasty poet, frequently depicted rural life and pastoral scenes in his work. Kim Jong-jik invokes this classical reference to elevate the modest country dwelling to the realm of poetic tradition.
  - key: ''
    value: The 'western valley' (西崦) refers to a specific locale in classical poetry associated with rustic simplicity and natural beauty.
